Package: nids-config
Version: 1.0.0
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Maayan App Developer <mapelboim@gmail.com>
Depends: python3 (>= 3.8), python3-yaml, iproute2
Description: NIDS Network Configuration Utility
 This package installs the nids-config tool used to configure 
 IPv4 and IPv6 protocol monitoring settings for Network 
 Intrusion Detection System (NIDS) environments.
 .
 Features:
  - Enable/disable IPv4 and IPv6 protocol monitoring
  - Auto-detect and configure network interfaces
  - Enable promiscuous mode for packet capture
  - Validate system environment for NIDS readiness
  - Persistent configuration in /etc/nids/config.yaml
 .
 The tool prepares Ubuntu 22.04 LTS systems to support
 NIDS applications by configuring network interfaces and
 protocol settings.